description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated, enthusiastic Band 7 Staff Podiatrist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours will be over 3 days per week at the Ilkeston Hospital site for a fixed term of 2 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as a member of the Ilkeston Podiatric Surgery team working in the Diagnostic and Treatment Centre and Outpatients at Ilkeston Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team focuses on outpatient and day case Podiatric Surgery. Therefore, it is essential that you have a keen interest and some experience in this field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your work will involve working with the Podiatric Surgery team within out-patients and theatre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to have HCPC registration and a Degree in Podiatry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you can demonstrate good communication skills, have the ability to plan, to organise, to be competent, and to deliver evidence based clinical care we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a clinical employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tim Kilmartin, Consultant Podiatric Surgeon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;timothy.kilmartin@nhs.net, 07850 004552&lt;/p&gt;
